<tr><td></td><td>Wolf In The Fold</td></tr>
<tr><td></td><td>TEASER</td></tr>
<tr><td></td><td>LOCATION--Cafe</td></tr>
<tr id="L1"><td><a href="#L1">1</a></td><td>ANNOTATION: A woman is doing a belly-dance, complete with finger-cymbals, while the patrons lounge on cushions. The audience are appreciating the show.</td></tr>

<tr id="L2"><td><a href="#L2">2</a></td><td>SCOTT:  Captain, I think I'm going to like Argelius.</td></tr>

<tr id="L3"><td><a href="#L3">3</a></td><td>KIRK:  Obviously a man of good taste.</td></tr>

<tr id="L4"><td><a href="#L4">4</a></td><td>SCOTT:  You mean to tell me all these women, that all this is</td></tr>

<tr id="L5"><td><a href="#L5">5</a></td><td>KIRK:  Yes, yes, yes. The Argelians think very highly of their pleasure.</td></tr>

<tr id="L6"><td><a href="#L6">6</a></td><td>MCCOY:  That's an understatement if I ever heard one. This is a completely hedonistic society.</td></tr>

<tr id="L7"><td><a href="#L7">7</a></td><td>KIRK:  Do you like her, Scotty?</td></tr>

<tr id="L8"><td><a href="#L8">8</a></td><td>SCOTT:  Aye. Why shouldn't I?</td></tr>

<tr id="L9"><td><a href="#L9">9</a></td><td>KIRK:  Good. I've invited her to join us at the table. I thought you might like to meet her.</td></tr>

<tr id="L10"><td><a href="#L10">10</a></td><td>SCOTT:  Now that's what I call a real Captain. Always thinking of his men.</td></tr>

<tr id="L11"><td><a href="#L11">11</a></td><td>ANNOTATION: The dancer comes over, bends over backwards then does a shimmy before returning to the small stage to finish. Scotty bangs on the table in applause.</td></tr>

<tr id="L12"><td><a href="#L12">12</a></td><td>KIRK:  Scotty, Scotty. In Argelius they use the lights.</td></tr>

<tr id="L13"><td><a href="#L13">13</a></td><td>SCOTT:  Now no one has to tell an old Aberdeen pub-crawler how to applaud, Captain.</td></tr>

<tr id="L14"><td><a href="#L14">14</a></td><td>ANNOTATION: She comes over, but the man at the next table doesn't look too pleased with the situation.</td></tr>

<tr id="L15"><td><a href="#L15">15</a></td><td>KIRK:  Have one of our pillows?</td></tr>

<tr id="L16"><td><a href="#L16">16</a></td><td>ANNOTATION: The man leaves as she sits.</td></tr>

<tr id="L17"><td><a href="#L17">17</a></td><td>SCOTT:  'Tis a fine foggy night tonight, and I doubt if anyone's ever told you of the marvellous fogs we have in Aberdeen.</td></tr>

<tr id="L18"><td><a href="#L18">18</a></td><td>KARA:  Never a word, but I'm dying to learn.</td></tr>

<tr id="L19"><td><a href="#L19">19</a></td><td>SCOTT:  Well then, why don't I show you? There's nothing like a walk in the fog with a bonny lass.</td></tr>

<tr id="L20"><td><a href="#L20">20</a></td><td>KARA:  Or a handsome gentleman. Why don't we?</td></tr>

<tr id="L21"><td><a href="#L21">21</a></td><td>SCOTT:  You don't mind, do you? I might even get back to the ship on time.</td></tr>

<tr id="L22"><td><a href="#L22">22</a></td><td>KIRK:  We won't leave without you, Scotty. Relax and enjoy yourself. (Scott and Kara leave) My work is never done.</td></tr>

<tr id="L23"><td><a href="#L23">23</a></td><td>MCCOY:  My work, Jim. This is prescription stuff. Don't forget, the explosion that threw Scotty against a bulkhead was caused by a woman.</td></tr>

<tr id="L24"><td><a href="#L24">24</a></td><td>KIRK:  Physically he's all right. Am I right in assuming that?</td></tr>

<tr id="L25"><td><a href="#L25">25</a></td><td>MCCOY:  Oh, yes, yes. As a matter of fact, considerable psychological damage could have been caused. For example, his total resentment toward women.</td></tr>

<tr id="L26"><td><a href="#L26">26</a></td><td>KIRK:  He seems he's overcoming his resentment.</td></tr>

<tr id="L27"><td><a href="#L27">27</a></td><td>MCCOY:  Of course, in my professional opinion, when he gets back to the ship, he's going to hate you for making him leave Argelius. But then he will have lost total resentment toward women.</td></tr>

<tr id="L28"><td><a href="#L28">28</a></td><td>KIRK:  Mission accomplished as far as Scotty is concerned. Bones, I know a little place across town where the women</td></tr>

<tr id="L29"><td><a href="#L29">29</a></td><td>MCCOY:  Oh yes. I know the place. Let's go.</td></tr>

<tr><td></td><td>LOCATION--Street</td></tr>
<tr id="L30"><td><a href="#L30">30</a></td><td>ANNOTATION: The fog hangs very low on Argelius - somewhere just below knee level. Couples are meandering along lost in each other. Kirk works out which way to go, then suddenly - a scream splits the night. They run towards it and find the dancer on the ground.</td></tr>

<tr id="L31"><td><a href="#L31">31</a></td><td>MCCOY:  She's dead, Jim.</td></tr>

<tr id="L32"><td><a href="#L32">32</a></td><td>KIRK:  Stabbed, a dozen times.</td></tr>

<tr id="L33"><td><a href="#L33">33</a></td><td>SOMEONE: (And standing by a wall, groaning, with a bloody knife in his hand, is Montgomery Scott.</td></tr>

<tr id="L34"><td><a href="#L34">34</a></td><td>SOMEONE: Captain's log, stardate 3614.9. Planet Argelius Two. While on therapeutic shore leave, Mister Scott has fallen under suspicion of having brutally murdered an Argelian woman. The chief city administrator, Mister Hengist, has taken charge of the investigation, but has learned little of value.</td></tr>

<tr><td></td><td>LOCATION--Cafe</td></tr>
<tr id="L35"><td><a href="#L35">35</a></td><td>HENGIST:  (a neat man in a suit) I don't know what to say, gentlemen. Argelius is the last planet in the galaxy I'd expect a thing like this to happen.</td></tr>

<tr id="L36"><td><a href="#L36">36</a></td><td>KIRK:  We're just as shocked as you are, Mister Hengist.</td></tr>

<tr id="L37"><td><a href="#L37">37</a></td><td>HENGIST:  If this was my home planet, Rigel Four, I'd have a dozen investigators working on the matter, but they don't exist here.</td></tr>

<tr id="L38"><td><a href="#L38">38</a></td><td>MCCOY:  You're not a native of Argelius, sir?</td></tr>

<tr id="L39"><td><a href="#L39">39</a></td><td>HENGIST:  Oh, no. Argelius hires its administrative officers from other planets. The Argelians aren't very efficient, you know. Gentle, harmless people. Mister Scott. Mister Scott? Now, are you sure you've never seen this before? (the knife)</td></tr>

<tr id="L40"><td><a href="#L40">40</a></td><td>SCOTT:  I, I don't remember.</td></tr>

<tr id="L41"><td><a href="#L41">41</a></td><td>HENGIST:  Really, sir. That is hardly helpful.</td></tr>

<tr id="L42"><td><a href="#L42">42</a></td><td>KIRK:  Scotty, you left the cafe with the girl. Do you remember that? What happened next?</td></tr>

<tr id="L43"><td><a href="#L43">43</a></td><td>SCOTT:  We were walking in the fog. I was up ahead trying to lead the way. I heard the girl scream. I remember starting to turn. I don't remember another thing.</td></tr>

<tr id="L44"><td><a href="#L44">44</a></td><td>KIRK:  Scotty, you've got to remember.</td></tr>

<tr id="L45"><td><a href="#L45">45</a></td><td>MCCOY:  Jim. (they move off a little way) If he says he can't remember, he probably doesn't. You know Scotty.</td></tr>

<tr id="L46"><td><a href="#L46">46</a></td><td>KIRK:  I know a murder's been committed.</td></tr>

<tr id="L47"><td><a href="#L47">47</a></td><td>MCCOY:  You don't think by any chance that Scotty</td></tr>

<tr id="L48"><td><a href="#L48">48</a></td><td>KIRK:  It doesn't make any difference what I think.</td></tr>

<tr id="L49"><td><a href="#L49">49</a></td><td>MCCOY:  But you don't just throw him to the wolves.</td></tr>

<tr id="L50"><td><a href="#L50">50</a></td><td>KIRK:  Bones, I have a diplomatic responsibility. This happened under Argelian jurisdiction. If they want to arrest him, try him, even convict him, I have to go along with it.</td></tr>

<tr id="L51"><td><a href="#L51">51</a></td><td>MCCOY:  But he's suffering from a severe concussion.</td></tr>

<tr id="L52"><td><a href="#L52">52</a></td><td>KIRK:  We'll do what we can.</td></tr>

<tr id="L53"><td><a href="#L53">53</a></td><td>HENGIST:  It's not promising, Captain. Mister Scott insists he remembers nothing, but my detector readings indicates that only his fingerprints are on the murder weapon.</td></tr>

<tr id="L54"><td><a href="#L54">54</a></td><td>KIRK:  Yes. Mister Hengist, there were other people in the cafe about the time of the murder. Several of them left just before Mister Scott and the girl did.</td></tr>

<tr id="L55"><td><a href="#L55">55</a></td><td>HENGIST:  So I've been informed by the staff. They're being located and we will question them. But the outlook for your friend is quite grim.</td></tr>

<tr id="L56"><td><a href="#L56">56</a></td><td>KIRK:  What's the law in these cases?</td></tr>

<tr id="L57"><td><a href="#L57">57</a></td><td>JARIS:  The law of Argelius is love.</td></tr>

<tr id="L58"><td><a href="#L58">58</a></td><td>ANNOTATION: An elegant grey-haired man enters, with a woman.</td></tr>

<tr id="L59"><td><a href="#L59">59</a></td><td>HENGIST:  Gentlemen, our prefect, Jaris. Sir, Captain Kirk, Doctor McCoy.</td></tr>

<tr id="L60"><td><a href="#L60">60</a></td><td>JARIS:  And this is my wife, Sybo.</td></tr>

<tr id="L61"><td><a href="#L61">61</a></td><td>HENGIST:  And this man is Scott, the one I sent you the message about.</td></tr>

<tr id="L62"><td><a href="#L62">62</a></td><td>JARIS:  He does not look like a man capable of such an act. Still, it's been so long. Gentlemen, before our great awakening two hundred years ago, we had ways of learning the truth in such matters. We shall return to them.</td></tr>

<tr id="L63"><td><a href="#L63">63</a></td><td>MCCOY:  The Argelian empathic contact?</td></tr>

<tr id="L64"><td><a href="#L64">64</a></td><td>JARIS:  You know of this?</td></tr>

<tr id="L65"><td><a href="#L65">65</a></td><td>KIRK:  Yes, we've heard of it. I assumed it was a lost art.</td></tr>

<tr id="L66"><td><a href="#L66">66</a></td><td>JARIS:  My wife is a descendent of the ancient priestesses of our land. She has the ancestral gift. Gentlemen, I have come to invite you to my home.</td></tr>

<tr id="L67"><td><a href="#L67">67</a></td><td>HENGIST:  Prefect, don't you think this should be handled in an official manner through my office?</td></tr>

<tr id="L68"><td><a href="#L68">68</a></td><td>JARIS:  It shall be handled in an official manner, Mister Hengist, since I am the highest official. Gentlemen, let us proceed to my home where, with the aid of my wife, we shall learn the truth. Please.</td></tr>

<tr><td></td><td>LOCATION--Jaris' home</td></tr>
<tr id="L69"><td><a href="#L69">69</a></td><td>ANNOTATION: The middle eastern theme continues with spiral columns, onion-dome arches, latticed windows and plenty of cushions.</td></tr>

<tr id="L70"><td><a href="#L70">70</a></td><td>KIRK:  Depending on your wife's empathic abilities is all very well, Prefect, but there's only one way we can find out what it is Mister Scott cannot remember. Since you find it impossible to let us go back up to our ship, I can beam down a technician with a psycho-tricorder.</td></tr>

<tr id="L71"><td><a href="#L71">71</a></td><td>MCCOY:  Prefect, it will give us a detailed account of everything that's happened to Mister Scott in the last twenty four hours.</td></tr>

<tr id="L72"><td><a href="#L72">72</a></td><td>HENGIST:  Oh, I'd advise against it, Prefect. This is purely an Argelian matter.</td></tr>

<tr id="L73"><td><a href="#L73">73</a></td><td>JARIS:  My wife must meditate for a time before she's ready. I see no reason why we should not use that time to good advantage. Very well, Captain.</td></tr>

<tr id="L74"><td><a href="#L74">74</a></td><td>KIRK:  Kirk to Enterprise.</td></tr>

<tr><td></td><td>LOCATION--Bridge</td></tr>
<tr id="L75"><td><a href="#L75">75</a></td><td>SPOCK:  Enterprise. Spock here.</td></tr>

<tr><td></td><td>LOCATION--Jaris' home</td></tr>
<tr id="L76"><td><a href="#L76">76</a></td><td>KIRK:  Mister Spock, beam down a technician with a psycho-tricorder, please. Use these co-ordinates.</td></tr>

<tr><td></td><td>LOCATION--Bridge</td></tr>
<tr id="L77"><td><a href="#L77">77</a></td><td>SPOCK:  Acknowledged. Co-ordinates received.</td></tr>

<tr><td></td><td>LOCATION--Jaris' home</td></tr>
<tr id="L78"><td><a href="#L78">78</a></td><td>KIRK:  Kirk out.</td></tr>

<tr id="L79"><td><a href="#L79">79</a></td><td>MCCOY:  Prefect, the psycho-tricorder will require privacy to be effective.</td></tr>

<tr id="L80"><td><a href="#L80">80</a></td><td>JARIS:  There is a small chamber below this room. Perhaps that will suffice. Captain, news of this frightful murder is spreading among my people. They're greatly disturbed. I have already heard talk of closing Argelius to space vehicles.</td></tr>

<tr id="L81"><td><a href="#L81">81</a></td><td>KIRK:  Well, that would be most unfortunate. Argelian hospitality is well-known, as well as its strategic importance as a space port.</td></tr>

<tr id="L82"><td><a href="#L82">82</a></td><td>JARIS:  Yes. I believe it's the only one in the quadrant. (hands out drinks) Captain.</td></tr>

<tr id="L83"><td><a href="#L83">83</a></td><td>HENGIST:  There are other people we should question. Perhaps I should go expedite their arrival here?</td></tr>

<tr id="L84"><td><a href="#L84">84</a></td><td>JARIS:  Yes, please do so, Mister Hengist. Anyone with any connection with this murder should be present at the ceremony.</td></tr>

<tr id="L85"><td><a href="#L85">85</a></td><td>ANNOTATION: A woman beams down as Hengist leaves.</td></tr>

<tr id="L86"><td><a href="#L86">86</a></td><td>KAREN:  Lieutenant Karen Tracy reporting as ordered, Captain.</td></tr>

<tr id="L87"><td><a href="#L87">87</a></td><td>KIRK:  Lieutenant, I want a twenty four hour regressive memory check made on Mister Scott.</td></tr>

<tr id="L88"><td><a href="#L88">88</a></td><td>KAREN:  Yes, Captain. Where shall I set up?</td></tr>

<tr id="L89"><td><a href="#L89">89</a></td><td>JARIS:  If you'll Just follow me, Lieutenant.</td></tr>

<tr id="L90"><td><a href="#L90">90</a></td><td>ANNOTATION: Jaris and Karen leave.</td></tr>

<tr id="L91"><td><a href="#L91">91</a></td><td>KIRK:  Scotty, co-operate completely with Lieutenant Tracy. Maybe we'll clear this thing up.</td></tr>

<tr id="L92"><td><a href="#L92">92</a></td><td>SCOTT:  I certainly hope so, sir. I can't stand this not knowing. (leaves)</td></tr>

<tr id="L93"><td><a href="#L93">93</a></td><td>MCCOY:  Captain, under normal conditions, Scotty would have never done such a thing.</td></tr>

<tr id="L94"><td><a href="#L94">94</a></td><td>KIRK:  But that blow on the head. It could put all his previous behaviour patterns into the junk heap.</td></tr>

<tr id="L95"><td><a href="#L95">95</a></td><td>MCCOY:  Of course, there's another possibility.</td></tr>

<tr id="L96"><td><a href="#L96">96</a></td><td>KIRK:  Explain.</td></tr>

<tr id="L97"><td><a href="#L97">97</a></td><td>MCCOY:  Hysterical amnesia. When a man feels guilty about something, something too terrible to remember, he blots it out of his conscious memory.</td></tr>

<tr id="L98"><td><a href="#L98">98</a></td><td>ANNOTATION: Jaris returns and crosses to another doorway.</td></tr>

<tr id="L99"><td><a href="#L99">99</a></td><td>JARIS:  Are you ready, Sybo?</td></tr>

<tr id="L100"><td><a href="#L100">100</a></td><td>SYBO:  I am ready. May I have the knife, please?</td></tr>

<tr id="L101"><td><a href="#L101">101</a></td><td>JARIS:  Certainly. Among other gifts, Sybo has the ability to receive impressions from inanimate objects. Do you have it, Captain?</td></tr>

<tr id="L102"><td><a href="#L102">102</a></td><td>KIRK:  The knife? No.</td></tr>

<tr id="L103"><td><a href="#L103">103</a></td><td>JARIS:  But I put it here when we arrived. It's gone.</td></tr>

<tr id="L104"><td><a href="#L104">104</a></td><td>ANNOTATION: A woman's scream fills the air.</td></tr>

<tr><td></td><td>LOCATION--Chamber</td></tr>
<tr id="L105"><td><a href="#L105">105</a></td><td>ANNOTATION: Karen Tracy is lying face down on the floor, and Scott is slumped unconscious in a chair.</td></tr>

<tr id="L106"><td><a href="#L106">106</a></td><td>KIRK:  Scotty.</td></tr>

<tr id="L107"><td><a href="#L107">107</a></td><td>MCCOY:  She's dead, Jim. Just like the other one.</td></tr>

<tr id="L108"><td><a href="#L108">108</a></td><td>KIRK:  Stabbed over and over again.</td></tr>

<tr><td></td><td>LOCATION--Jaris' home</td></tr>
<tr id="L109"><td><a href="#L109">109</a></td><td>JARIS:  (to Scott) Drink this. An Argelian stimulant, Doctor. Quite effective and quite harmless.</td></tr>

<tr id="L110"><td><a href="#L110">110</a></td><td>MCCOY:  Go ahead, Scotty.</td></tr>

<tr id="L111"><td><a href="#L111">111</a></td><td>SCOTT:  Lieutenant? Captain? Where's</td></tr>

<tr id="L112"><td><a href="#L112">112</a></td><td>KIRK:  Lieutenant Tracy is dead, Scott. You were found alone in the room.</td></tr>

<tr id="L113"><td><a href="#L113">113</a></td><td>SCOTT:  Dead? But I</td></tr>

<tr id="L114"><td><a href="#L114">114</a></td><td>KIRK:  What happened down there?</td></tr>

<tr id="L115"><td><a href="#L115">115</a></td><td>SCOTT:  I was sitting there. She was taking her readings, and now I'm sitting here.</td></tr>

<tr id="L116"><td><a href="#L116">116</a></td><td>MCCOY:  Is that all that happened?</td></tr>

<tr id="L117"><td><a href="#L117">117</a></td><td>SCOTT:  I tell you, I don't remember. I must have passed out.</td></tr>

<tr id="L118"><td><a href="#L118">118</a></td><td>MCCOY:  It could be, Jim. That head injury.</td></tr>

<tr id="L119"><td><a href="#L119">119</a></td><td>KIRK:  That head injury. Think, Scotty.</td></tr>

<tr id="L120"><td><a href="#L120">120</a></td><td>SCOTT:  Captain, I've been trying. I can't even believe this is really happening.</td></tr>

<tr id="L121"><td><a href="#L121">121</a></td><td>KIRK:  There's no way into that place from up here. Prefect, is there another entrance to that chamber?</td></tr>

<tr id="L122"><td><a href="#L122">122</a></td><td>JARIS:  Yes, there's a door that leads into the garden, but it's been locked for years.</td></tr>

<tr id="L123"><td><a href="#L123">123</a></td><td>MCCOY:  Locks can be picked, Jim.</td></tr>

<tr id="L124"><td><a href="#L124">124</a></td><td>KIRK:  Check it.</td></tr>

<tr id="L125"><td><a href="#L125">125</a></td><td>ANNOTATION: McCoy leaves and Hengist enters. He is accompanied by the man from the next table and one of the musicians.</td></tr>

<tr id="L126"><td><a href="#L126">126</a></td><td>HENGIST:  Prefect, both of these men were at the cafe the night of the murder.</td></tr>

<tr id="L127"><td><a href="#L127">127</a></td><td>KIRK:  Where've they been during the past few minutes?</td></tr>

<tr id="L128"><td><a href="#L128">128</a></td><td>HENGIST:  Captain, if you don't mind please.</td></tr>

<tr id="L129"><td><a href="#L129">129</a></td><td>KIRK:  There's been another murder, Hengist. One of my crew.</td></tr>

<tr id="L130"><td><a href="#L130">130</a></td><td>JARIS:  The same as Kara.</td></tr>

<tr id="L131"><td><a href="#L131">131</a></td><td>HENGIST:  Why, that's terrible. (to the man from the next table) You, my men picked you up near there. What were you doing?</td></tr>

<tr id="L132"><td><a href="#L132">132</a></td><td>MORLA:  Please, I know nothing about it. I didn't kill anyone.</td></tr>

<tr id="L133"><td><a href="#L133">133</a></td><td>HENGIST:  Well, how was the girl killed?</td></tr>

<tr id="L134"><td><a href="#L134">134</a></td><td>KIRK:  Stabbed. And there's no sign of the weapon.</td></tr>

<tr id="L135"><td><a href="#L135">135</a></td><td>HENGIST:  If only I had facilities.</td></tr>

<tr id="L136"><td><a href="#L136">136</a></td><td>KIRK:  You. You were a musician at the cafe. You played for the murdered girl.</td></tr>

<tr id="L137"><td><a href="#L137">137</a></td><td>TARK:  Since she was a little girl, she danced for me. She was my daughter. Prefect, how could this thing have happened here? The man who did it must be found. He must be punished.</td></tr>

<tr id="L138"><td><a href="#L138">138</a></td><td>KIRK:  And you. You left the cafe before Scott and Kara.</td></tr>

<tr id="L139"><td><a href="#L139">139</a></td><td>JARIS:  Is this true? Who are you?</td></tr>

<tr id="L140"><td><a href="#L140">140</a></td><td>MORLA:  Morla of Cantaba Street, Prefect. I was there. I have nothing to hide.</td></tr>

<tr id="L141"><td><a href="#L141">141</a></td><td>KIRK:  Did you know Kara?</td></tr>

<tr id="L142"><td><a href="#L142">142</a></td><td>TARK:  Of course he knew her. They were to be married, but he behaved disgracefully. Unheard of. He was jealous of her.</td></tr>

<tr id="L143"><td><a href="#L143">143</a></td><td>JARIS:  That is very disquieting.</td></tr>

<tr id="L144"><td><a href="#L144">144</a></td><td>MORLA:  I know it was wrong, but I just couldn't help myself. I loved her, and when she went over to the table with these men, I could not stand to watch, so I left and went home.</td></tr>

<tr id="L145"><td><a href="#L145">145</a></td><td>KIRK:  Jealousy has often been a motive for murder.</td></tr>

<tr id="L146"><td><a href="#L146">146</a></td><td>JARIS:  Yes, I know. That is why the emotion is so strongly disapproved of here.</td></tr>

<tr id="L147"><td><a href="#L147">147</a></td><td>MORLA:  Prefect, I didn't kill anyone. I couldn't.</td></tr>

<tr id="L148"><td><a href="#L148">148</a></td><td>JARIS:  We shall see, Morla.</td></tr>

<tr id="L149"><td><a href="#L149">149</a></td><td>MCCOY:  Sorry, Jim. The lock may or may not have been picked. It would be hard to tell even with the tricorder.</td></tr>

<tr id="L150"><td><a href="#L150">150</a></td><td>KIRK:  Can you prove you went directly home?</td></tr>

<tr id="L151"><td><a href="#L151">151</a></td><td>HENGIST:  Captain, may I continue with the questions please?</td></tr>

<tr id="L152"><td><a href="#L152">152</a></td><td>KIRK:  Well get on with it, man. Just don't stand there.</td></tr>

